item.description:
@Cheesehunk wrote:

[quote=“The Un-Named, post:12, topic:32446”][quote author=Hellfish link=topic=47039.msg593979#msg593979 date=1165708061]

how about

OpenWebPage(‘www.google.com’);

that opens them in default browser (firefox ;D)

You need http:\ else it won’t open.

I have a better version of the script that wouldn’t open webpages using the OpenWebPage(); function. And now I know why. lol
[/quote]

Yeah, without http:\ SCAR won’t recognize it as a webpage and attempt to open it, and of course it’s opening a web page it hasn’t been allowed so it won’t open. I’ve found no way to not use http:\ even with adding the sites into the firewall, unfortunately.[/quote]

Haha, I think he meant because the Computer is already lagging terribly. I could be wrong though.

item.dc:creator: @The_Un-Named The Un-Named
item.description:
@The_Un-Named wrote:

[quote=“Hellfish, post:11, topic:32446”][quote author=The Un-Named link=topic=47039.msg589964#msg589964 date=1165652736]

how about

OpenWebPage(‘www.google.com’);

that opens them in default browser (firefox ;D)

You need http:\ else it won’t open.
[/quote]

I have a better version of the script that wouldn’t open webpages using the OpenWebPage(); function. And now I know why. lol[/quote]

Yeah, without http:\ SCAR won’t recognize it as a webpage and attempt to open it, and of course it’s opening a web page it hasn’t been allowed so it won’t open. I’ve found no way to not use http:\ even with adding the sites into the firewall, unfortunately.

X Lag is script I just finished making.

It lags by using 3 methods:
Opening web pages, without waits.
Bitmap loading, again, without waits.
Computing random numbers with a 400th(?) of a second wait(Credits to Martin).

It moves the mouse randomly for fun(Credits to Ron)!

USE WITH CAUTION!!

[scar]{.Script Info:

ScriptName = X Lag

Author = Hellfish

Description = Lagger using numerous methods

Version = 1.0

Date = Dec. 5

Comments = USE WITH CAUTION!!!

/Script Info}
program xlag;
//The juice for the machine
var
randomomg, j, jj, play : integer;
writetest : string;

procedure webpage;
begin
//Web page opening nexus!
getpage(‘www.google.ca’);
getpage(‘www.moparisthebest.com/smf’);
getpage(‘www.freewebs.com/horndragon’);
getpage(‘www.projectw.org’);
getpage(‘en.wikipedia.org’);
end;

Procedure CrazyMouse;
Var k : Integer;
Begin
// Get your clients dimensions.
GetClientDimensions(x2, y2);
// For k equals 1 to 10 do this…
For k := 1 to 10 do
Begin
// Move mouse randomly
MoveMouse(Random(x2), Random(y2));
// Add 1 to k each time until it equals 10.
k := k + 1;
End;
End;
